In the words of @perrywhite.la “All day long we criticize the parts of our body that we want to make better and we never focus on the parts of ourselves that are amazing.” ✨
⠀
Perry hand picked this outfit for me to wear to the Grammys and I opened up to him that it really triggered my body dysmorphia…that I struggle with accepting parts of myself. I wanted to go with one of his leather pieces that covered the parts of me that I struggle accepting. This is the real life speech he gave me about why I needed to embrace myself and wear this piece. He asked me what I stood for. He told me to stop playing it safe. He helped me remember that my every day choices reflect either what is comfortable and safe or what is uncomfortable and purposeful.
⠀
It was in this moment I decided F#%# IT - I can’t keep waiting for the day that I all of a sudden “LOOK” like what I think is beautiful or perfect. I am built the way I am. And I can’t live another second not enjoying fashion and life just because I don’t feel good about the shape of my body. It’s not the message I spread, it’s not what I stand for. I was a classic case of “a preacher not following his own teachings”
⠀
Thank you @perrywhite.la for not just being an incredible designer with an incredible story, but for being an incredible human and creating from a place of love that this world is starving for. You made my first Grammy experience one I will most definitely cherish. ✨💛
⠀

Grammys 2023 ✨
⠀
I went with my main squeeze, growing partner, and love @andy_darling_ae thank you @drehilton for giving us the opportunity to have this experience. What a powerful memory and all the people I got to experience it with and through.
⠀
Everything in life can be a catalyst for the next best version of you. You just have to build the self awareness to harness it. This definitely gave me some juice 🥤 for the rest of the year to remember what I touched and what I’m grinding for. Which is just my authentic passions and joys to be actualized and mirrored back by the universe through people and impact.  I am is grateful to this life and the power of creation in its truest form.
⠀

This song is called “Stay Blue” it’s  9 years old. it’s been about that long since I wrote all my music solely on piano. It’s been a wild journey of self discovery and self abandonment. When you’re so hungry to shed skin and transform into the person you’ve always wanted to be, sometimes you shed parts of you that were your secret weapon, your special sauce, your golden egg, your unique perspective gift…..those things can get lost in the name of evolving so it’s important to look inward and take stock.
⠀
I’ve been running from parts of myself for a while now. Only recently becoming aware of how uncomfortable going back to my natural state was.
⠀
I’ll probably be speaking on this more and more but for now this is where my thought ends for today. Hope you enjoy this song and glimpse of the me I hide behind that fierce BADASS chick named Phenix Red.
⠀

It’s crazy to think that how we see ourselves could never be the same as how other people see us. We only see ourselves in photos or videos or the mirror……never eye to eye. Never outside of our own eyes and mind.
⠀
Sometimes it really trips me out because I’ll see a picture and I’ll be like IS THAT REALLY ME? Sometimes in a good way and sometimes in a bad way. Just crazy the power of perception.
⠀
I have always thought  the polar opposite of me to be the most beautiful. Darker skin. darker hair. Darker eyes. Slender and petite. So I always have compared myself to that.
⠀
It’s taken me a long time to just accept that I am built the way I’m built and I might as well embrace it and learn to love it otherwise it’ll be a long next 60 ish years. 😅
⠀
The self love journey is a wild plot in the experience of being human. 🌸
